Ys I & II (イースI・II, Īsu Wan Tsū) is a Japanese action role-playing video game compilation for the PC Engine CD-ROM² System released in 1989 by Hudson Soft/NEC. It consist of enhanced remakes of the first two Ys games developed and published by Nihon Falcom for the NEC PC-8801 home computer in Japan. It was released as Ys Book I & II for the TurboGrafx-CD in North America in 1990, and was a pack-in title for the TurboDuo in 1992.
Ys I & II was released on the Virtual Console in Japan on October 16, 2007, in North America on August 25, 2008,[6] and in Europe and Australia on September 5, 2008.



